<TITLE> 2 more police stations in Sylhet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 11 (bdnews24.com)  Two more police stations, at Shahparan and the airport, will be set up in Sylhet metropolitan area next year. Finance minister AMA Muhit said Sunday that the stations will be set up as the government is pledge-bound to ensure people's security. The initiative has been taken to ensure safety of the people, he said addressing a meeting organised by the Awami League. The minister also inaugurated the Mahaldig Bridge on the Salutikar-Shahebbazar-Haripur highway. On electricity and gas crises, the minister said it would take time to overcome the situation. "But the government has been working sincerely to resolve the situation." "The government is determined to meet the basic demands of the people. But the government should be given time," said Muhith. bdnew
